Self-motivated, detail oriented, strong sense of responsibility and multi-tasked

We are a well-established property leasing, management and investment company located in Wanchai-Admiralty area, now inviting an experienced candidate for the position of Assistant Accountant/Senior Accounts Assistant.

Responsibilities:

Handle full sets of account independently;
Handle daily accounting works;
Book keeping and accounting data entry;
Assist in month-end closing and ad hoc duties assigned by supervisors;
Assist in management of accounting filing system.


Requirements: 

Higher Diploma in accounting or related disciplines;
At least 5 years accounting experience;
Proficiency in MS office and Flex system is a must;
Able to meet reporting deadlines and work under pressure;
Initiative, well organized and self-motivated
Experience in system implementation/change

We offer an attractive remuneration package and excellent career prospects to the right candidate.  Please send full resume, current and expected salary, contact number and the availability to us for interview.

Personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.

Job Responsibilities:

Responsible daily accounting operation and administrative matters;
Prepare bank reconciliations monthly;
Prepare month-end & year-end documents;
Prepare auditing documents to auditor annually:
Maintain efficient filing of accounting records;
Responsible stock management;
Provide support to ad hoc tasks as assigned.
Requirements:

Form 5 or DSE graduate with LCCI Level 2 or above (fresh graduated may be considered);
Prefer 2 -3 years relevant accounting & administration experience;
Knowledge in DacEasy / MYOB system will be preferable;
Familiar with EXCEL and MS Office;
Team player, pro-active, willing to meet challenge and learn attitude;
Good command in spoken and written Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
Immediate available would be highly preferred.

 We offer 5-day work with attractive salary and fringe benefits to the right candidate.

 Please send your full resume with availability, current & expected salary to HR Department.

 Responsibilities:

Responsible for daily accounting operations and month end closing;
Prepare management reports, financial analysis and monthly consolidation reporting packages;
Assist in budget & forecast and audit & tax issues;
Perform ad hoc projects / assignments as required


 Requirements:

Bachelor in Accounting with professional accounting qualification;
Minimum 5 years solid accounting experience, preferably in freight forwarding industry;
Proficient in accounting systems (preferably Oracle) and Microsoft Office;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese, Mandarin is an advantage;
Self-motivated, detail-minded, good team player and able to work under pressure;
Immediate availability is highly preferred;
Candidates with lower qualification / less experience will be considered as Assistant Accountant.

Interested parties please send your detailed resume and expected salary to Human Resources and Administration Department, Hutchison Logistics (HK) Limited (i) by fax to 3544-3530;  or (ii) by email. Please visit our website http://www.hutchisonlogistics.com/ for further details. 

We are an equal opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. The information provided will be treated in strict confidence and used only for consideration of application for relevant /similar positions within the Hutchison Group of Companies. Applicants not invited for interview in 6 weeks after job posting may consider their application unsuccessful and your personal data will be destroyed after a period of 6 months.

Responsibilities:

Analyzing monthly and quarterly management reports of various subsidiaries located in Hong Kong, Singapore and PRC, and preparing GAAP adjustments for consolidation purpose;
Assist in quarterly group consolidation, semi-annual and annual results announcement in Singapore Stock Exchange, and Annual Report preparation work;
Participate in annual budgeting and cash flow forecasting process and ad-hoc assignments;
Liaise with auditors in connection with annual audit process.

Requirements:

Degree holder in accounting or related disciplines;
Member of professional accounting bodies or equivalent;
Minimum 4 years' relevant working experience or audit experience (preferably gained from sizable CPA firm);
Exposure in the PRC accounting and tax regulations is an advantage;
Hardworking, meticulous, able to work well under pressure and to meet tight reporting deadlines;
Strong analytical skill & problem solving skill with proactive attitude and able to work independently are required;
Proficiency in Cantonese, English and Mandarin;
Immediate available is preferred;
Travelling to PRC is NOT required.

Working on the headquarter level in Hong Kong (Admiralty Office), we offer 5 days work and attractive remuneration package to right candidate.  Interested parties please email your full resume with availability, current and expected salary to us.

Responsibilities

Assist in handle assignments independently;
Involving in public offerings, listings, due diligence and private placements;
Assist in analyze financial results of clients’ companies;
Assist in providing support to clients regarding different regulatory regimes, listing rules and related regulations;
Keep up-to-date on regulatory developments;
Assist in preparing business plans and IPO business proposals; Developing effective business relationships with clients;
Handle ad hoc matters assigned.

Requirements

Higher Diploma in accounting or related discipline.
Student member of HKICPA/ACCA/CPAA or other relevant professional bodies;
0-1 year of accounting/audit experience in any field;
Self-motivated, willing to take job ownership, manage deadlines and able to work as a team player;
Proficient in MS Excel and word and knowledge of computerized accounting system is highly preferred;
Good analytical, interpersonal and communication skill is highly preferred;
Good command in written and spoken English, Chinese and Mandarin;
Business travel is required;
Fresh graduates are welcome;
Immediate available is preferred.

